Third-party attributions
================================================================================

This product contains code derived from the **Music Synthesizer for Android**
(MSFA), an open-source DX7 emulator originally written by Raph Levien and
contributors:

    https://github.com/google/music-synthesizer-for-android

MSFA is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. A copy of that license
is reproduced below.

The DSP code in this project that is derived from MSFA consists of ROM lookup
tables and the integer arithmetic that uses them. These are reimplementations
in Rust — no MSFA C++ source code is reproduced verbatim. The provenance is
documented in source comments next to each ported piece (search for
"MSFA / Dexed" in `src/`). The relevant items are:

  - `AMS_SCALE_TABLE`     in `src/operator.rs`   (from `ampmodsenstab[4]`)
  - `EXP_SCALE_DATA`      in `src/operator.rs`   (from `exp_scale_data[33]`)
  - `VELOCITY_DATA`       in `src/operator.rs`   (from `velocity_data[64]`)
  - `calculate_key_level_factor()`  — port of MSFA `ScaleLevel` / `ScaleCurve`
  - `update_cached_values` velocity branch — port of MSFA `ScaleVelocity`
  - `PMS_TABLE`           in `src/fm_synth.rs`   (from `pitchmodsenstab[8]`)
  - `LFO_FREQ_TABLE`      in `src/lfo.rs`        (from `lfoSource[100]`)
  - `PITCHENV_RATE`       in `src/pitch_eg.rs`   (from `pitchenv_rate[100]`)
  - `PITCHENV_TAB`        in `src/pitch_eg.rs`   (from `pitchenv_tab[100]`)

Acknowledgements also to **Dexed** (https://github.com/asb2m10/dexed) by
Pascal Gauthier, which embeds and extends MSFA, and to the
**dx7-patches** repository (https://github.com/itsjoesullivan/dx7-patches)
whose JSON schema is the input format for this project's preset loader.

